headline: Grand Forks' UAS industry by the numbers
summary: Aug. 23—GRAND FORKS — In 2014, the Grand Forks Herald reported that the Association for Unmanned Vehicle Systems International estimated that some 100,000 UAS-related jobs would be created in the U.S. by 2025 and would create an economic impact of $82 billion. At that time, AUVSI also projected that North Dakota would see more than 100 new jobs and an economic impact of $10.2 million because ...
